[290] Francis Jeake to Joseph Tucker, 22 September 1716. Original letter. ESRO FRE 5382

London Saturday Sept. 22 1716 Honoured Sir, I went yesterday to Mr Gybbon, who happened to be gone out, so to day morning I went again, & went very luckily, for the man who had the Bill from Mr Sharp came within two minutes after me, so I received the money which I paid to my Brother, & the Bill which J now send you. Mr Gybbon gives his Service to you, my Mother & Sister, & says that he would have writ this Post
